# bat config. "ansi" is bat's built-in 16-color theme: it maps syntax tokens
# onto the terminal's ANSI slots, which tinted-shell retints live on every
# `theme` switch. So `cat`/`bat` (and anything reading this config) follows the
# active tinty scheme instead of a pinned palette. Matches the television
# previews, which already force BAT_THEME=ansi.
--theme="ansi"
--style="numbers,changes,header"
--paging=auto
